t: Psalm 71
In*p thee, O Lord,*s do I put my trust: let me never be put to confusion.
Deliver*p me in thy righteousness, and cause me to escape: incline thine ear unto me, and save me.
Be*p thou my strong habitation, whereunto I may continually resort: thou hast given commandment to save me; for thou art my rock and my fortress.
Deliver*p me, O my God, out of the hand of the wicked, out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.
For*p thou art my hope, O Lord God:*s thou art my trust from my youth.
By*p thee have I been holden up from the womb: thou art he that took me out of my mother's bowels: my praise shall be continually of thee.
I*p am as a wonder unto many; but thou art my strong refuge.
Let*p my mouth be filled with thy praise and with thy honour all the day.
Cast*p me not off in the time of old age; forsake me not when my strength faileth.
For*p mine enemies speak against me; and they that lay wait for my soul take counsel together,
Saying,*p God hath forsaken him: persecute and take him; for there is none to deliver him.
O*p God, be not far from me: O my God, make haste for my help.
Let*p them be confounded and consumed that are adversaries to my soul; let them be covered with reproach and dishonour that seek my hurt.
But*p I will hope continually, and will yet praise thee more and more.
My*p mouth shall shew forth thy righteousness and thy salvation all the day; for I know not the numbers thereof.
I*p will go in the strength of the Lord God:*s I will make mention of thy righteousness, even of thine only.
O*p God, thou hast taught me from my youth: and hitherto have I declared thy wondrous works.
Now*p also when I am old and grayheaded, O God, forsake me not; until I have shewed thy strength unto this generation, and thy power to every one that is to come.
Thy*p righteousness also, O God, is very high, who hast done great things: O God, who is like unto thee!
Thou,*p which hast shewed me great and sore troubles, shalt quicken me again, and shalt bring me up again from the depths of the earth.
Thou*p shalt increase my greatness, and comfort me on every side.
I*p will also praise thee with the psaltery, even thy truth, O my God: unto thee will I sing with the harp, O thou Holy One of Israel.
My*p lips shall greatly rejoice when I sing unto thee; and my soul, which thou hast redeemed.
My*p tongue also shall talk of thy righteousness all the day long: for they are confounded, for they are brought unto shame, that seek my hurt.
